
XPATH:-
           a] XPATH stands for 'XML' path.
           b] Xpath is used to find the location of any element on a webpage using HTML DOM structure.
           c] It was defined by world wide web consortium(W3C).
           d] Xpath is used to navigate the nodes in any XML/HTML document.

SYNTAX

         Xpath =//tagname[@Attribute='value']

 There are 2 types of Xpath

 1]Absolute Xpath
                   It contains the complete path from the root element of page to the desired element.
                   It starts with root node.
                   Any slight change in DOM makes the absolute xpath invalid.

2]Relative Xpath
                  Relative xpath can start from any node in HTML DOM.
                  It begins with double forward slash (//)
                  It is less brittle compared to Absolute Xpath.

XPATH with and & or Operator.

Syntax -
            Xpath = //tagName[@Attribute = 'value' or @Attribute = 'value']

            Xpath = //tagName[@Attribute = 'value' and @Attribute = 'value']

   -----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

Xpath Axes Methods

 It represents the relationship to the context node.

 1]Parent:-
            It is used to find the parent of current nod.

   Syntax:-

            Xpath = //tagName[@Attribute='value']//parent::tagName

  2]child:-
            It selects all children of current node

  Syntax

           Xpath = //tagName[@Attribute='value']//child::tagName

           xpath = //div[@id='nav-xshop']//child::a[5]

   3] Self:-
              It selects the current node.

    Syntax:-

             Xpath = //tagName[@Attribute='value']//self::tagName
-----------------------------------------------------------------------------------

DESCENDANTS, DESCENDANTS-OR-SELF

DESCENDANTS:-
                It selects all the descendants like (Children, GrandChildren) of the context(current) node.

                //tagName[@Attribute='value']//descendant::tagName

                //tagName[@Attribute='value']//descendant::tagName[@Attribute='value']


DESCENDANTS-OR-SELF:-

                It selects the context(current) node & all its descendants like (Children, GrandChildren).
                 If tagName for descendants & self are same.

Syntax:-        //tagName[@Attribute='value']//descendant-or-self::tagName

------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

Ancestor, Ancestor-or-self

Ancestor:-
            It selects all the ancestors [parent, grandparents, etc] of current node

Syntax:-
          //tagName[@Attribute='value']//ancestor::tagName

Ancestor-or-self:

                     It selects all the ancestors [parent, grandparents, etc] of current node.
                     If tagName for ancestors & self are same.


Syntax:-
          //tagName[@Attribute='value']//ancestor-or-self::tagName.
---------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

following, following-sibling

following:-
            It selects all the nodes that appears after the current(Context)node.

Syntax:-
           //tagName[@Attribute='value']//following::tagName

following-sibling:-

           It selects all the nodes that have the same parent as the context(current) node.

 Syntax:-
            //tagName[@Attribute='value']//following-sibling::tagName

 -----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------



